<div class="project-container">
  <h1>Introducing new speed limit e-scooter</h1>
  <div class="project-description">
    <div class="img-scooter"></div>
    <div class="project-content">
      <div class="project-table">
        <table>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Industry</strong></td>
              <td>automotive, e-mobility</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Challenge</strong></td>
              <td>adapt product to local market</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Role</strong></td>
              <td>project lead, research, operations, branding</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div class="case-summary">
        <h2>Description</h2>
        <p>Going live in a new country with your product is exciting. Copying your entry strategy from one country to the other should always be carefully considered.
        For one of the new markets where we introduced the e-scooter it soon became clear that customers expected more options. Especially when it came down to choosing the speed limit of their vehicle. Analyzing market data, customer feedback and performing surveys and interviews we realized to have a bigger impact we needed to introduce the extra option: the 25km/h e-scooter was introduced.
        It had a positive impact on reaching new customers and partners and increased sales numbers within the first weeks after launching the new product. </p>
      </div>
    </div>
