<div class="project-container travel-insurance">
  <h1>Flexible and modular travel insurance</h1>
  <div class="project-description">
    <div class="project-content">
      <div class="project-table">
         <table>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Industry</strong></td>
              <td>insurance, digital</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Challenge</strong></td>
              <td>create flexible insurance modules adaptable to personal needs</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Role</strong></td>
              <td>facilitation, research, prototype</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div class="case-summary">
        <h2>Description</h2>
        <p>What do people expect to be covered by their insurance and maybe more importantly, what do they not want to pay extra for?
        That was one of the main questions we wanted to get answered. Customers do not want the traditional insurance anymore where the insurance company dictates what you get covered. They want to be in control.
        Through performing extensive market research with more than 1000 EU respondents we discovered that the most important module for travel insurance is the benefit of receiving medical <strong>assistance</strong>.
        A travel insurance was created where people could pay per day, cancel per day and sign up anytime to receive medical assistance. The customer is in control and decides.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="img-travel"></div>
  </div>
</div>
